{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, this has significant value in building natural human-computer interaction systems (Wani et al. 2021).",
    "Therefore, future research can focus on analyzing the special emotional features in dialect speech, building emotional speech datasets, and optimizing emotion recognition algorithms.",
    "For instance, Cheng et al. (2021) constructed a Henan dialect speech emotion database, which includes five emotions: happiness, surprise, sadness, anger, and neutrality.",
    "The effectiveness of the dataset was verified using different network models.",
    "The experimental results showed that the average recognition rate of the Learning Vector Quantization (LVQ) neural network was the highest."
  ]
}